Local Repo

1.cd project_folder

2.git init - Initializes Local Repo-.git hidden folder appears

3.git add,rm --cached files ( git add *.html to add all html files, git add . to add all files) - Files in stagings

4.git status to check - Reports files that have changed

5.git commit - Goes to vim editor kind of mode. Press I for insert mode and type in commit message. Esc+:wq takes you out. In nano use Ctrl+X and Enter. Now status shows nothing coz all files are comitted.
 OR
git commit -m "Message" to skip all the vim,nano stages.


6. .gitignore - Folder/Document that contains filenames to be ignored
touch .gitignore
Open it and put all filenames which have to be ignored

7. git branch branchname - To create new branch
   git checkout branchname - To switch branches
   git merge branchname - To megre branch with master
   Make changes in branches and merge finally


Remote Repo-github

1. Create repo in github
2. git remote add origin "url"
3. git push -u origin master
4. git pull - To reflect changes made by others contributors on your local repo.

Cloning
1.Open new folder 
2.git clone 'url'
